         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne botanic Gardens ¶ January 16th 1865 ¶ Sir ¶  ¶ I have the honor to submit to your favorable consideration the desirability of the portion of land near the City bridge and now occupied as pas...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">65.01.16</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Wardell</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">M65/722, unit 97, VPRS 3991/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>First registered in the Public Works Office as No. 242, unit 12, p. 301, VPRS 963, PROV, then forwarded to the Chief Secretary.<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>
                  </p>
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; font-weight: bold; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation '<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>L661<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>| with Dr Mueller | 1.2.65'. Does this refer to outward correspondence?</p>
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">I can</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">'t comment usefully in this, but L661 appears no</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">w</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">here else in correspondence we have</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>Melbourne botanic Gardens</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">January 16th 1865</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the honor to submit to your favorable consideration the desirability of the portion of land near the City bridge and now occupied as pasture ground of the Immigrant Home being rendered available for planting operations during the forthcoming season, the locality referred to being not only so accessible from the City and therefore so eligible for tree plantations, but also comprising the best soil in the Reserve. It seems to me moreover highly desirable, that no time should be lost in raising trees on the spot for the ornamentation of the City landscape and in anticipation of the ground being required as part of the Government House Domain.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Should my views meet with your approbation, I would arrange for the required earth work being immediately commenced and would solicit, that the temporary concession of occupying the ground as pasture land be withdrawn and that the cows of the Immigrants Home be transferred to the Government Reserve at Sunbury, from whence as long as the Immigrants Home can still be retained in the Government House domain, the milk could readily be brought to that establishment.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On 19 January Wardell minuted: 'Will The Hon The Chief Secretary be pleased to state whether he will consent to Dr. Muellers request with respect to the removal of the Cows to Sunbury'<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">.</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>For decision on the request see notes to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">a duplicate of this letter</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">M to J. McCulloch, 16 January 1865 (in this edition as 65-01-16a),<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your most obedient</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Mueller.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS written by Ernst Heyne and signed by M.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">W. Wardell Esq.</p>
         </div>
